headline: Accenture to buy Australian cybersecurity firm CyberCX for reported $650 million
summary: Accenture said on Thursday it will buy Australian cybersecurity firm CyberCX in its largest-ever deal in the sector, with the Australian Financial Review valuing the transaction at more than A$1 billion ($650 million). A wave of devastating cyberattacks has battered Australia, including a 2022 breach at telecom major Optus that exposed the personal data of up to 10 million users, and a hack on health insurer Medibank affecting nearly 10 million customers. In July, Qantas Airways disclosed that criminals had infiltrated one of its call centres, accessing personal information of six million customers.

headline: Accenture to Acquire CyberCX, Expanding Cybersecurity Capabilities in Asia Pacific
summary: NEW YORK & MELBOURNE, Australia, August 15, 2025--Accenture has agreed to acquire CyberCX, a leading privately-owned cybersecurity services provider.
